summary:
My name is Anatoliy Shchadin, and I have experience in legal support of a mining project in Madagascar, a construction project on a Russian scale, as well as significant litigation in Russian arbitration. I am preparing clear legal opinions and is able to carry out an examination of almost any contract.

I am currently looking for a job and would be grateful for reviewing my CV. I am sure that my versatile experience and professional competencies can benefit the future employer.

A few details about myself:

- Graduated from St. Petersburg State University in 2014, Bachelor of Laws;
- experience in the direction
more than 8 years;
- knowledge of all blocks of legal work (corporate, contract, claim);
- experience of litigation in Russian courts (arbitration courts, courts of general jurisdiction of all instances);
- experience in full legal support of an international project for the extraction of chromium (Madagascar);
- the skill of preparing legal opinions on various issues;
- experience of interaction with public authorities;
- knowledge of English and French.

I would be glad to have the opportunity to tell you more about my professional experience.

profile_positions.description:
- creation of foreign legal entities:
preparation of a set of documents in French,
search for offices and conclusion of lease agreements,
contribution of funds to the authorized capital,
submission/receipt of documents to the registration authority;
- opening of current accounts in foreign banks (Bank of Africa (BOA), Banque Nationale d'Investissement (BNI);
- development of tax schemes:
analysis of legislation,
preparation of recommendations on the choice of tax systems,
negotiations with officials of the Ministry of Finance of Madagascar on the possibility of signing an agreement on the avoidance of double taxation;
- Preparation of a cooperation agreement and concession agreements with the state company of Madagascar in the mining sector;
- participation in negotiations;
- Preparation of legal opinions on international, tax, labor, mining, contract, administrative law of Madagascar;
- formation of a legal position for the Supreme Constitutional Court and the National Anti-Corruption Committee of Madagascar at the request of the director of the joint company;
- registration of mining rights
verification of licenses in the Office of the Mining Cadastre of Madagascar,
registration of transfer of rights to licenses in accordance with the concession agreement,
payment of license fees;
- organization of transportation, customs clearance at the port and departure of cargo:
preparation of transport contracts, business
trips to the international port of Madagascar (Tuamasina) for processing documents necessary for the export of products,
negotiations with representatives of the customs service of Madagascar and customs brokers,
control over the procedure for filling containers with products and weighing them.
My role in the project is to act as the only lawyer with a permanent presence on Madagascar and report to the Director of the legal department in the central office, as well as to act as a manager during his absence.

- claim and claim work (formation of a legal position on each case, risk assessment, preparation of claims, preparation and submission of claims, counterclaims, reviews, petitions, appeals and cassation complaints through My Arbitrator);
- contract work (development of contract forms, contract schemes, legal expertise of contracts).
My role in the project is to provide high-quality and complete judicial protection of client companies in arbitration courts from writing a claim to making a decision on the case.

Results and achievements:
- successfully conducted claims and claims work against contractors who carried out routine repairs of the facilities of the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation;
- >50 claims were filed (including counterclaims), for which more than 100 million rubles were collected from counterparties;
- experience of representation in the arbitration court of Moscow, St. Petersburg and Leningrad region, Sevastopol, Kaliningrad region, 9, 13 arbitration courts of appeal, the arbitration Court of the Moscow District;

Examples of court cases from practice: A40-236831/2017, A40-159433/2017, A40-74245/2018, A40-30152/2018, A40-232900/2017, A40-242339/2018, A40-209407/2018, A40-187139/2017, A56-69038/2017, A56-6195/2019
